OL,3,CHospital admits to 'failings' in care
OL,4,Cof autistic boy who died of sepsis
OL,6,F"Sometimes I think is my child the
OL,7,Fonly autistic child in the world
OL,8,Fbecause have you not seen this before?
OL,9,FThey should know better."
OL,11,FMr Vieira believes staff did not
OL,12,Funderstand his son's behaviour.
OL,13,FMattheus was non verbal and so unable
OL,14,Fto articulate his distress.
OL,16,FObservations were dismissed as
OL,17,F"inaccurate" by some medical staff. In
OL,18,Ffact, they were accurate and indicated
OL,19,Fthat his kidney infection had
OL,20,Fdeveloped into septic shock.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G4/9
