OL,3,CHospital admits to 'failings' in care
OL,4,Cof autistic boy who died of sepsis
OL,6,F"In particular, it is admitted that
OL,7,Fthere was a delay in diagnosing life-
OL,8,Fthreatening sepsis and that there was
OL,9,Fa subsequent failure to adequately
OL,10,Fmanage sepsis.
OL,12,F"It is further admitted that, on the
OL,13,Fbalance of probabilities, Mattheus
OL,14,Fwould not have died but for those
OL,15,Ffailings in his care.
OL,17,F"It is accepted it is likely that,
OL,18,Fwith adequate resuscitation, Mattheus
OL,19,Fwould have made a full recovery."
